01/02/2005
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- Chief UN war crimes prosecutor Carla del Ponte begins a three-day trip to the Balkans on Tuesday (1 February), planning stops in Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) and Serbia-Montenegro.
Aides say the visits will be aimed at ensuring the arrest of fugitive suspects.
In Sarajevo, Del Ponte will hold talks with High Representative Paddy Ashdown on a common strategy for apprehending two of the tribunal's top indictees, Radovan Karadzic and Ratko Mladic.
(Danas - 01/02/05;
Fena, Beta - 31/01/05)
